      "text": [
        " مَنْ نَظَرَ إِلَى ثَمَنِهِ وَ هُوَ يُوزَنُ لَمْ يُفْلِحْ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibrahim Bin Uqba, from Muhammad Bin Mysar, from his father, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who looks at his price and he is being weighed, would not succeed’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "15. A number of our people have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from Ibrahim ibn ‘Uqbah from Muhammad ibn Muyassir from his father who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘One who looks at his own price when he is weighed, he does not succeed.’” "
        ]
      }
